From Rick Miller Subject How to Make Your Own X Face in x C Easy Steps Will someone who can 'see' the X Face included in this header please reply and tell me if it turned out okay I'm not all too sure about my viewing software I hand converted this thing in vi from a Sun rasterfile what a pain For folks who haven't the slightest, it went like this How to Make Your Own X Face in x F Easy Steps Scan my Drivers' License into a PCX file Use WinGIF to 'trim' my face out of the license, 'reduce' it by half, and convert it to BMP Use Paintbrush to touch up manually Use WinGIF to 'reduce' it by half again Use Paintbrush to touch up again Use WinGIF to 'reduce' it by half again and convert it to GIF now over to the UNIX side Use Snapshot to convert the GIF to a Sun rasterfile Use IconEdit to touch it up and convert it to an X bitmap Use vi yes, a text editor to manually convert the rasterfile into the Uncompressed X Face format Lots of global ed commands, and by the time you're done you'll mirror hex bytewise in your sleep now over to the Linux side A Use compface to convert it to what you see here A m Dob BO 'E ,EEQGbn qy En aS U k G HIbY X PD szF vVxCXSn mw G nVHE W, X j s r zs O HFU LwzYgH B Try viewing it by whatever means you have available C Go back to step , but do it right this time Rick Miller Ricxjo Muelisto Send a postcard, get one back Enposxtigu bildkarton kaj vi ricevos alion RICK MILLER WOODS MUSKEGO, WIS USA